    "client_msg_id": "fc53d449-fbec-4706-918b-2b488a344c54",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Interesting references, thanks <@UA14TGLTC>!\n\nI'll add a more historical one: the earliest detailed discussion of computation in domain notations is a 1979 article by Terry Winograd: <https://doi.org/10.1145/359131.359133>. Winograd distinguishes between the \"subject domain\" (what we tend to call just \"domain\" today), the \"domain of interaction\" (basically UI) and the \"domain of implementation\" (code).",
    "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
    "ts": "1622015078.026200",
