    "client_msg_id": "f7eb58e9-08ad-4488-9d2e-fc9699b414f2",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "A flash insight resulting from summarizing Ivan Illich's \"Tools for conviviality\" to a colleague right after writing my last comment in this thread: bikeshedding is a symptom of non-convivial technology. Bikeshedding happens when people focus on what they understand best, rather on what matters most. With convivial technology, both should coincide.",
    "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
    "ts": "1622015256.021600",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
